reviewText: In That's My Baby, Tim Jones and his girl friend Betty try to pull her dad out of a deep blue funk. He is on the verge of suicide and is cheered up by a series of musical numbers, performed by the likes of bandleader Freddie "Schnickelfritz" Fisher and pianist Gene Rogers. A2ZCDS did a great job in remastering this classic. The picture and sound quality is great for a film of its age.
